&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GAQ227R1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work at the nexus of law and innovation with a recognized global leader in Data and AI.&amp;nbsp; As a Databricks Legal Intern, you won’t just observe, you’ll jump straight into novel legal issues working alongside our high-impact global legal team. You will gain first-hand experience on how an in-house legal department drives business strategy and tackles complex challenges on a daily basis, and navigate cutting-edge legal landscape of generative AI, cloud computing, and big data.&amp;nbsp; Databricks will encourage you to get out of your comfort zone and provide the resources, mentoring, and feedback you need to grow your legal skills and career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid, in-person position located in our San Francisco and Mountain View offices.&amp;nbsp; The position offers exposure to a variety of legal practice areas and allows for potential deep dives of areas including: Commercial and Go-to-Market, Privacy, IP, Product &amp;amp; Privacy, Legal Compliance &amp;amp; Ethics, Corporate, Employment &amp;amp; Litigation, and others. You and our other legal interns will work with mentors within Legal as well as join our summer 2026 intern cohort where you&#39;ll have the opportunity to connect with other interns, cross-functional teams and leaders not just within our department, but across the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The impact you will have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with various Databricks Legal teams to support all areas of our business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and teach our Legal department about novel legal issues, especially as they relate to AI and cloud technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Further Legal strategy and objectives through the development of critical work product and/or assets that will inform future initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to mission-critical projects and initiatives across a variety of practice areas, including Commercial and Go-to-Market, Privacy, IP, Product &amp;amp; Privacy, Legal Compliance &amp;amp; Ethics, Corporate, Employment &amp;amp; Litigation, and others to gain broad exposure to our business and operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help Databricks continue to balance legal risks as it continues on its exciting path forward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled as a 1st-year (1L) or 2nd-year (2L) law student (graduating in summer 2027 or summer 2028), with a strong record of academic performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eagerness to learn about Databricks technology and new legal issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to roll-up your sleeves and tackle tough problems with the full support of our team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work both independently and with colleagues as needed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional legal research, analytical, and organizational skills, along with a strong foundation in advocacy and judgment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-level legal drafting skills that is consistent with current legal education and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A desire to be part of a dynamic legal team supporting the recognized leader in processing big data in the cloud&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior background or strong interest in technology, data analytics and Artificial Intelligence (preferred but not required)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Program Details:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internship program starts on June 8, 2026 and ends August 7, 2026&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Position is full-time (40 hours per week)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is a hybrid, in-person role, requiring a minimum of three days per week in our San Francisco or Mountain View offices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applications will be accepted on a rolling basis through mid- to late- February; interviews may begin as early as mid-January&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Application packages should include:&amp;nbsp; resume, law school transcript, undergraduate transcript, law school writing sample, and a cover letter describing why you are interested in Databricks and this program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
