&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the internship:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Customer Success Team at Okta ensures our customers achieve their business goals using our technology. We bridge the gap between Okta’s innovations and our customers’ priorities, driving long-term value and strategic alignment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Okta Customer Success Intern will be involved in all stages of the customer journey: onboarding, deployment, product adoption, and renewal. You will gain hands-on experience in how a Customer Success professional strategically partners with global brands to maximise their outcomes with Okta.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will gain experience in:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business: &lt;/strong&gt;Mapping the customer journey from initial setup to full adoption; learning Customer Success concepts like recurring revenue (ARR), ROI, and success planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical: &lt;/strong&gt;Building knowledge in Identity Access Management (IAM) and Zero Trust; the opportunity to earn your Okta Professional Certification; and applying AI to CS best practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Functional: &lt;/strong&gt;Developing presentation skills for executives; communicating technical concepts clearly; and collaborating with cross-functional teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Get Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn to communicate the business value of Okta’s products and solutions through presentations and storytelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Observe Customer Success Managers to understand onboarding plans, competitive landscapes, and IAM best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn the Scale Customer Success motion and playbook.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with teams like Sales, Engineering, Renewals, Marketing and Customer Advocacy to drive measurable business outcomes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Academic Journey:&lt;/strong&gt; Currently pursuing a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree with a graduation date between December 2026 and Summer 2027.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem Solvers:&lt;/strong&gt; A proactive learner with a sharp eye for detail and the ability to solve complex problems through data and analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; A strong communicator and storyteller, comfortable presenting ideas and research to diverse audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously, from performing market research to generating actionable reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech Passion:&lt;/strong&gt; A genuine interest in building a career within the SaaS/Cloud space, with a specific curiosity for how Identity secures the world’s leading brands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Availability:&lt;/strong&gt; Able to commit to a full-time 12-week internship (Summer 2026).&lt;/p&gt;
