&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual to join our Marketing Technology (MarTech) team. You will be embedded within the Marketing Strategy &amp;amp; Operations organization, which manages over 65 tech tools and the end-to-end data flow for millions of leads. This role is perfect for a detail-oriented problem solver who is eager to learn how a world-class enterprise scales its marketing engine through automation and data hygiene. You will work closely with cross-functional partners to streamline our digital infrastructure and explore the future of AI in marketing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Get to Do :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize Digital Infrastructure: Audit and reorganize our MarTech digital assets and cloud storage systems to ensure peak team efficiency and better data retrieval.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Process Excellence: Document end-to-end MarTech processes and create clear guidelines for documentation management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain Data Integrity: Support the team with critical data hygiene tasks and manage access requests for our extensive suite of marketing tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovate with AI: Research and evaluate emerging AI tools for content generation and data analysis, potentially contributing to proof-of-concept AI projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate Across Teams: Work directly with Marketing leads to support the tech lifecycle and ensure seamless software integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MarTech Stretch Project: You’ll have the opportunity to work on a project where you’ll get to collaborate with multiple teams, propose a solution to a complex problem, and present your findings and recommendations to Senior Leadership.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We are Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently pursuing a Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business Analytics, Information Systems, or a related field with a graduation date of Dec. 2026 or May/June 2027&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organizational Powerhouse: You have a meticulous approach to file management and a proven ability to handle complex data entry with high accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective Communicator: You can distill technical processes into clear written documentation and collaborate confidently in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curious &amp;amp; Proactive: You are a self-starter who is genuinely excited about exploring new technologies, specifically the application of AI within business operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;What you can look forward to as a Full-Time Okta employee!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
